{
  "title": "Crystalarium",
  "source": "stardewvalleywiki",
  "sections": [
    {
      "heading": "Introduction",
      "content": "The Crystalarium is a crafted item that will replicate any inserted Gem (except Prismatic Shard ), Foraged Mineral , or Geode Mineral . The functions of the Crystalarium are explained in the Lost Book Technology Report! .\nOne Crystalarium is the reward for donating 50 Minerals to the Museum . One Crystalarium is also the reward for completing the 25,000 Bundle in the Vault . Occasionally it can be found in a treasure room in the Skull Cavern.\nOnce an item is inserted, it will replicate that item an infinite number of times. Once a gem or mineral has been inserted into the Crystalarium, it can be retrieved at any time by removing the Crystalarium with a tool."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Use",
      "content": "Note that times to craft are approximate, since time passes differently from 2am to 6am. One hour = 60 minutes from 6am to 2am, but 1 hour = 100 minutes from 2am to 6am. One full day is 1600 minutes, where day is 1200 minutes and night is 400 minutes."
    },
    {
      "heading": "Tips",
      "content": "- Crystalariums can be used to replicate minerals en masse that can be traded at the Desert Trader for helpful items or gifted to villagers as loved or liked gifts."
    },
    {
      "heading": "History",
      "content": "- 1.3.27 : Removed an exploit that replaced a ready-to-harvest mineral with a more expensive mineral.\n- 1.4 : Can now be stacked in a player's inventory and in chests .\n- 1.5 : Removing a Crystalarium that isn't ready for harvest will now drop the gem that was placed in it.\n- 1.6 : Inserting a new gem into a Crystalarium now pops the previous one out, instead of silently replacing it."
    }
  ],
